-- PulteGroup profit falls 8 pct as home deliveries fall
-- By Sagarika Jaisinghani in Bangalore
-- Thu Apr 24, 2014 06:44AM EDT
-- None



April 24 (Reuters) - PulteGroup Inc <PHM.N>, the No. 2 U.S. homebuilder, reported an 8 percent drop in quarterly profit as it handed over fewer homes to buyers and said orders fell 6 percent.

The company's net income dropped to $74.8 million, or 19 cents per share, in the first quarter ended March 31 from $81.8 million, or 21 cents per share, a year earlier. [ID:nPnc1Q20b]